,"1384–1423":"1384–1423","1322–Male":"1322–Deceased","1330–Female":"1330–Deceased","Abt 1384":"about 1384","1423":"1423","1322":"1322","1355":"1355","1375":"1375","1352":"1352","1330":"1330","1384":"1384","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","about 1375":"about 1375","1390":"1390","Hillmorton, Warwickshire, England":"Hillmorton, Warwickshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Astley","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of several places in England called Astley (in Lancashire, Shropshire, Warwickshire, Worcestershire, and Yorkshire), from Old English <i>ēast</i> ‘east’ + <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’. The modern surname seems to be particularly associated with the one in Warwickshire. See also   Astle  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Astle","meanings":["English: habitational name from a place in Cheshire called Astle, from Old English <i>ēast</i> ‘east’ + <i>hyll</i> ‘hill’. There may also have been some confusion with <i>Asthall</i> and   Astley  . Or occasionally this may be a topographic name denoting residence on an ‘east hill’ (from Middle English <i>ast</i> + <i>hill</i> or <i>hull</i>), i.e. a hill to the east of a settlement.","English: perhaps also a habitational name from Astwell, Northamptonshire, from Old English <i>ēast</i> ‘east’ + <i>wielle</i> ‘spring’.","English: habitational name from Asthall, Oxfordshire, from Old English <i>ēast</i> ‘east’ + <i>halh</i> ‘nook’."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":30,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas Astley was born in 1352, in Hillmorton, Warwickshire, England, his father, Ralph Astley, was 30 and his mother, Agnes Gerbridge, was 22. He had at least 2 sons with Catherine Bacon. He died in 1384, in his hometown, at the age of 32."},"et":{"1352–1384":"1352–1384","1355–Female":"1355–Surnud","1340–1390":"1340–1390","–Female":"Surnud","1375–Male":"1375–Surnud","1384–1423":"1384–1423","1322–Male":"1322–Surnud","1330–Female":"1330–Surnud","Abt 1384":"umbes 1384","1423":"1423","1322":"1322","1355":"1355","1375":"1375","1352":"1352","1330":"1330","1384":"1384","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","about 1375":"umbes 1375","1390":"1390","Hillmorton, Warwickshire, England":"Hillmorton, Warwickshire, England"},"fi":{"1352–1384":"1352–1384","1355–Female":"1355–Kuollut","1340–1390":"1340–1390","–Female":"Kuollut","1375–Male":"1375–Kuollut","1384–1423":"1384–1423","1322–Male":"1322–Kuollut","1330–Female":"1330–Kuollut","Abt 1384":"noin 1384","1423":"1423","1322":"1322","1355":"1355","1375":"1375","1352":"1352","1330":"1330","1384":"1384","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","about 1375":"noin 1375","1390":"1390","Hillmorton, Warwickshire, England":"Hillmorton, Warwickshire, England"},"fr":{"1352–1384":"1352–1384","1355–Female":"1355–Décédée","1340–1390":"1340–1390","–Female":"Décédée","1375–Male":"1375–Décédé","1384–1423":"1384–1423","1322–Male":"1322–Décédé","1330–Female":"1330–Décédée","Abt 1384":"environ 1384","1423":"1423","1322":"1322","1355":"1355","1375":"13